name: Fishermen of Patzcuaro
description:
Lake Pátzcuaro is a lake in the state of Michoacán, in Mexico, one of the highest in the world and considered one of the most beautiful. It has an area of 260 square kilometers, with a length of 55 km and a width of 34 km.

Lake Pátzcuaro is one of the most visited tourist attractions in the area, rich in archaeological, historical, recreational and cultural sites of the Purépecha ethnic group. It is recognized for its artisanal fishing with butterfly wing nets, which leaves us very peculiar pictures.
